1
00:00:00,220 --> 00:00:07,540
Well, we thought, starting with the image of Black, like the Spinal Tap album.

2
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:10,140
Alright, here we go.

3
00:00:10,140 --> 00:00:15,400
So, okay, for those of you film buffs, I wanted to use Back in Black.

4
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:23,980
Marvel has never paid the, you know, six-figure price for it, and I think we ended up, to save money, not actually having

5
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:29,300
credits run over the song. Do we want this fucking light on the whole time?

6
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,980
My kids are here.

7
00:00:38,340 --> 00:00:41,840
So you see there's no music playing.

8
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:45,900
See? Now once the credits go off, watch what happens.

9
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:53,630
There you go.

10
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:57,300
We saved $150,000.

11
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:02,345
Oh, we gotta crank this up - you're killing me.

12
00:01:02,345 --> 00:01:07,550
We'll go a little bit more - we're loud. So this is actually in Lone Pine, California.

13
00:01:07,550 --> 00:01:11,800
And that's not an Arab, but it is a Mexican with a goat.

14
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,450
Just let this play, it's too good.

15
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:23,150
We re-cut this scene about 50,000 times.

16
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:26,650
There he is.

17
00:01:27,270 --> 00:01:30,810
I'm actually chewing Nicorette gum right there.

18
00:01:30,810 --> 00:01:33,482
Much of this is improvised.

19
00:01:33,482 --> 00:01:42,090
There are other versions of this where he's dancing to Tom Jones singing Prince's Kiss.

20
00:01:42,090 --> 00:01:44,530
We went a different way.

21
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:49,590
Robert and I were constantly fighting about whether or not Tony Stark would wear a tie.

22
00:01:49,590 --> 00:01:55,950
And so you'll see that sometimes the button's open, sometimes the tie's up, sometimes the tie's down.

23
00:01:55,950 --> 00:02:03,330
Jon, no offense, I can't hear myself in this scene. You gotta crank it up, this is too good.

24
00:02:16,330 --> 00:02:23,870
So we wanted to here create a sense that we weren't really taking the setting of the war seriously.

25
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:26,025
He's joking, you're having a good time...

26
00:02:26,025 --> 00:02:29,810
Then in the back of this frame, it was very hard to get the explosion to

27
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:36,270
go off without tipping it. So if you look, hopefully you're not expecting it.

28
00:02:38,130 --> 00:02:43,300
We wanted to have a tonal shift in the film.

29
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:51,650
Jon actually pushed the button on that detonation.

30
00:02:51,650 --> 00:03:01,290
And I was riding in that Humvee behind them with a helmet on, and they pulled me aside, and he says, I have to tell you...

31
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:11,000
Can you turn it down a little bit? He says, I have to tell you, you can really get hurt.

32
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:15,179
I said, I don't understand, you told me it was safe in all the meetings.

33
00:03:15,179 --> 00:03:18,290
He says, yeah, it is safe. We did everything we could.

34
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:21,282
But you can get very hurt if something goes wrong.

35
00:03:21,282 --> 00:03:26,010
I just have to tell you that. And I said, so like, do you tell me not to do it?

36
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:33,170
He says, no, do it. I just have to tell you - You can really get hurt. The phone was my idea. Yes, it was.

37
00:03:33,170 --> 00:03:34,850
Oh, this was a fun day.

38
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:40,350
Yeah, we threw the... We kept throwing stuff in his face. We kept blowing an air mortar in his face.

39
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:41,624
It never happened quite right.

40
00:03:41,624 --> 00:03:45,190
This is actually a visual effect. Not totally happy with the way that it turned out.

41
00:03:45,190 --> 00:03:48,410
We did 12 fittings for this vest.

42
00:03:48,410 --> 00:03:49,110
Yeah.

43
00:03:49,110 --> 00:03:52,450
For me to lie on my back wearing it. There it is.

44
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,550
The vest.

45
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:05,230
So, here he is waking up. So that was sort of the vision. You start off with him joking around, having

46
00:04:05,230 --> 00:04:08,370
a cocktail, a suit, looking like a fish out of water.

47
00:04:08,370 --> 00:04:11,570
And then, boom, you're at a beheading video.

48
00:04:12,930 --> 00:04:14,922
And that was going to tell you.

49
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:20,000
That somewhere between those two... Between those two things, that's our story.

50
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:26,310
Is Matty Libatique here tonight, Jon? Is Matty here? I saw Matty today - I told him to stop by.

51
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:31,050
I haven't seen him. Fantastic Director of Photography.

52
00:04:31,050 --> 00:04:35,070
Real pictures of Robert.

53
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:41,410
I like that. Bill Gates.

54
00:04:42,670 --> 00:04:50,270
So many meetings about every frame of this thing. Because there's so much backstory in here.

55
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:55,170
Most of this is based on what's in the comic books.

56
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:03,670
I was just in Japan promoting the movie.

57
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:10,050
And somebody told me that was, what we just saw was the best part of the movie.

58
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:11,810
And I didn't even put it together -

59
00:05:11,810 --> 00:05:13,770
it was Kyle Cooper.

60
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:17,270
Very talented guy. I like that. Nice touch.

61
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:20,410
Rolling Stones thing.

62
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:24,470
Looks like the Republican National Convention.

63
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:31,150
We sort of wanted an upbeat feel.

64
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:38,770
This was actually not shot in Caesars Palace. But we had to show the logo from Caesars Palace.

65
00:05:38,770 --> 00:05:42,910
Otherwise they were going to hit us with a big bill for shooting in Caesars Palace.

66
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:47,450
This was in The Biltmore, downtown [L.A.] and then we added the podium.

67
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:50,550
So I saved another $100,000.

68
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:59,200
Okay, this theme song that we recorded is the theme song from the 60's Iron Man cartoon.

69
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,410
Not many people caught that.

70
00:06:02,410 --> 00:06:05,890
And we used it again in the casino in another version.

71
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:10,530
So this is... I hate to ruin it for you guys. This guy ends up being the bad guy,

72
00:06:10,530 --> 00:06:12,030
Jeff Bridges.

73
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:20,770
And this is where we sort of have to set up a little bit that he's jealous.

74
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:24,050
Also later in the film as well.

75
00:06:24,330 --> 00:06:31,870
To somehow create a paper cutout of a motive to justify the big fight at the end.

76
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:39,791
It took him about 8 hours to shave his head, a 16th of an inch at a time.

77
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:42,510
And I sat with him in the makeup trailer

78
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:45,270
As he got comfortable with it.

79
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:48,830
Here's me. Jon Favreau, ladies and gentlemen.

80
00:06:50,770 --> 00:06:53,450
Everybody thought this was Hilary Swank.

81
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:57,490
And there was internet rumors. But it actually isn't Hilary Swank.

82
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:05,090
This was pretty much improvised. This was our last day of filming in Vegas.

83
00:07:05,090 --> 00:07:08,730
With real casino goers gathered around. Remember that?

84
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:13,130
And Vince Vaughn was actually there off camera watching, cheering us on.

85
00:07:15,090 --> 00:07:19,110
I was very adamant that we use real chocolate chips. The $5,000 chips.

86
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:22,230
So they had to have it.

87
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:24,890
A few million dollars on the table there.

88
00:07:24,890 --> 00:07:32,190
The prop guy wanted to use fake ones. I said, no, I can't. Jon Favreau can't do a Vegas movie with fake chips.

89
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:37,670
When we were done shooting, we shot a suicide split from midnight to noon.

90
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:39,510
I remember that Vince was there.

91
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:44,130
And Jon took off his tux. He just had his t-shirt on. And it literally looked like a snapshot from

92
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:47,130
Swingers at one point.

93
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:51,170
I, of course, wasn't in Swingers...

94
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:58,630
This was the scene that he did in his screen test. And he killed it. It was even better than this.

95
00:07:58,630 --> 00:08:00,470
He never hit that level.

96
00:08:00,470 --> 00:08:05,150
And the first scene in the movie was a screen test scene too. Which he actually, by the time we were

97
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:12,550
shooting the first scene, he was just giving me good lines over a walkie-talkie. I think that's on the DVD.

98
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:15,730
I think the screen test scenes are on the DVD.

99
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,370
I thought everything was.

100
00:08:28,890 --> 00:08:35,030
This is how Tony Stark handles liberal journalists... coming up.

101
00:08:35,789 --> 00:08:38,550
A little shot there.

102
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,830
That's right, bitch.

103
00:08:57,330 --> 00:09:03,210
So there you go. We have the James Bond fantasy. How many different ways did we shoot this?

104
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:05,990
There's one where she slaps him.

105
00:09:06,410 --> 00:09:09,970
Remember she slapped you once? Do I remember!?

106
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:15,850
She slapped me! So that's the scene that I had to re-cut 15 times.

107
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:25,070
Not because the rating was bad, but because the language of some sexual or sensual content

108
00:09:25,070 --> 00:09:29,830
was unacceptable to Paramount and Marvel. Not the rating, but the language.

109
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:33,970
That ILM did. Isn't that great? I mean, it's fantastic.

110
00:09:33,970 --> 00:09:35,810
I hate CGI.

111
00:09:35,830 --> 00:09:41,000
But I was on their ass, and I'm happy with that. I think they really nailed it.

112
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:48,770
We added some movement in the water. People go crazy looking for this house at at Point Dume.

113
00:09:48,770 --> 00:09:55,000
I love it. I did seem to me they should have advertised it, "with some ceiling damage."

114
00:09:55,030 --> 00:10:02,070
We put an ad with that photo in the LA Times real estate section. And if you went to the website, it

115
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:05,350
took you to the Iron Man thing.

116
00:10:08,010 --> 00:10:10,590
Here's Gwyneth on a broken leg.

117
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:41,390
Now this is my real hot rod, and Robert decided instead of gapping the spark plugs, that he wanted to rip the engine block

118
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,890
apart.

119
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:46,570
There it is. Look at him.

120
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:51,090
Jay Leno said, it's clear that that guy does not know what he's doing.

121
00:10:51,090 --> 00:10:54,530
I said, I know, it's my car.

122
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:57,478
And Paul Bettany's voice . He did a favor for me.

123
00:10:57,478 --> 00:11:01,690
I met him on Wimbledon. Jarvis, the computer, is Paul Bettany's voice.

124
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:04,430
I love this scene.

125
00:11:42,450 --> 00:11:48,150
So that little bit of dialogue... about her correcting him about the springs period -

126
00:11:48,150 --> 00:11:53,030
was actually Gwyneth correcting me when she read the script. She says, no, it's actually not the spring

127
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:55,330
period. It's springs period.

128
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:58,830
I said, this is too good. I've gotta put this in.

129
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:04,290
I love it when somebody's trying not to be condescending but can't help it.

130
00:12:04,290 --> 00:12:06,610
And I love Gwyneth.

131
00:12:06,610 --> 00:12:11,210
She's a wonderful influence on the set. Great person. I've known her for many years.

132
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:16,890
But you can definitely tell that she has that culture. There is some chemistry going on right there.

133
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:26,060
Robert made us add this last little moment here.

134
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:30,840
Because if they were just looking at one another, it would have been too much. He had to walk away.

135
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,720
I handed her my espresso cup.

136
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,760
She's my assistant.

137
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,800
Here's the R8.

138
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,300
Okay, so see this R8?

139
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:42,100
We smashed up two of them.

140
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,520
For the ending.

141
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:46,140
And I cut it out of the movie.

142
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:49,860
And the Audi people said, wait a second.

143
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:53,046
We gave you a quarter million dollars worth of cars to...

144
00:12:53,046 --> 00:12:58,400
bounced the waiting list... So you could do what you cut out of the movie and say it didn't work.

145
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:00,620
I love the tail on this [plane] though.

146
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:03,240
Very happy with that CGI.

147
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:08,060
You guys see how little Happy Hogan says?

148
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:14,200
I thought I had more to do, but I cut myself out.

149
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,820
Here's a little improvised bit. Here are two cameras.

150
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:49,280
We shot all these scenes in six hours.

151
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,040
That's what I'm talking about.

152
00:13:55,540 --> 00:14:01,180
So, Ghostface Killer, who is known as Iron Man in the rap community, wanted to be a part of this.

153
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:06,780
We filmed the scene, cut it out, but I included him. And this is actually a song he made

154
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:08,520
for Iron Man.

155
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:12,550
And we made our own little video with him in the background for...

156
00:14:12,550 --> 00:14:15,420
Jon suggested they put in that dance pole.

157
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:16,920
Yeah.

158
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:22,700
Once again, back in Lone Pine.

159
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:26,560
Everything you've seen so far except for Vegas is in California.

160
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:29,500
Very adamant about shooting here.

161
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:41,500
So, this next bit here...

162
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:44,000
I'm very proud of it.

163
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:48,380
We wrote it five minutes before we shot it.

164
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:48,930
It's true.

165
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:54,540
The reason I'm wearing sunglasses is because Jon said, "cut, I see your eyes reading the cue cards."

166
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:59,820
We were scribbling on pieces of foam core.

167
00:15:00,180 --> 00:15:04,380
I love it. And by the way, at Comic-Con...

168
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:15,640
We don't play that part in Japan.

169
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:27,000
You know, for China, we had to cut everything out. We had to cut so much out, they

170
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,980
don't even ask you.

171
00:15:28,980 --> 00:15:33,880
They're like, you can't mention Genghis Khan. Genghis Khan? Really?

172
00:15:35,540 --> 00:15:39,720
That's the only country we had to change it. The reason this effect is good is because

173
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:43,020
I rode them like a jockey.

174
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,900
That's good.

175
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:52,640
I think we could have done better on that one.

176
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:56,660
I like that. There's a prop man under that pushing it up.

177
00:15:58,620 --> 00:16:01,420
Russell Bobbitt. That's true.

178
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:07,000
Marvel got very mad he didn't have his shirt on.

179
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:12,380
But then they gave us the great line, "Why aren't you wearing those pajamas I bought you?" It makes no sense.

180
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:15,280
It was really important to us.

181
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:22,500
Another improvised line.

182
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:25,036
Peter [Billingsley] said, that won't make sense.

183
00:16:25,036 --> 00:16:30,160
Nobody will understand what a Funvee and a Humdrumvee is. He said, okay, we're going to shoot it.

184
00:16:30,980 --> 00:16:37,560
This is a little magic, you see here - Dan Lebental magic. The cinematographer and editor.

185
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,420
So now we're back into real time.

186
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,700
This was our first shot. Correct.

187
00:16:55,700 --> 00:17:03,460
We had the entire cave, which was built on a stage out of mostly styrofoam, believe it or not.

188
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:05,180
Isn't that nice there?

189
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:06,680
Thank you.

190
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:12,800
Another one of my bright ideas.

191
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:19,040
And we refrigerated the whole set just to get that breath.

192
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:21,420
Just to get that breath.

193
00:17:21,420 --> 00:17:25,040
It gives it a nice little thing. We back off a bit a few scenes in.

194
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:31,560
I thought it was always a good idea to make sure that half your cast and crew have the flu before you go on to

195
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:36,440
the next bit of shooting.

196
00:17:45,110 --> 00:17:50,090
We shot pretty much in continuity, starting from here.

197
00:17:54,850 --> 00:18:02,070
It's a culmination of about 800 hours of meetings looking at drawings of what that thing should look like.

198
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:12,080
Robert was our technical advisor for how you

199
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:16,860
handle yourself in small, confined quarters.

200
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,440
Not a joke. He'd come in and say that's how you cook your thing and you need

201
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,440
a sock to make it.

202
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:26,280
It's good to know that.

203
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:30,900
Too soon?

204
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:35,000
Is it too soon?

205
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,660
Too soon.

206
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:39,620
It's sad.

207
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:57,300
He was from Crash, by the way - Shaun Taub. Shaun Taub - love him. The most Hollywood guy on the set.

208
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:22,500
So this guy here, Sayed, came in auditioning for the other role.

209
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:28,300
There was only one role for the bad guy.
I loved him so much.

210
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:32,600
He's actually friends with my wife's—
my wife works with somebody who's a nurse

211
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,900
who's his wife.

212
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:36,660
And you know those stories like,
"Can you just meet with the guy?

213
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:40,250
I work with his wife, here's a headshot." Yeah, bring him on.

214
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:43,640
He blew me away. He's like an Egyptian theatre actor,

215
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,600
and he was just a great dude.

216
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:49,420
And I was like, we gotta figure out how to get him in the movie.

217
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:54,735
And so we divided the bad guy up into two roles, and one of them is him.

218
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:57,540
And we actually shot a lot more stuff,

219
00:19:57,540 --> 00:20:04,558
where they became friends, remember, and he actually got bumped off by the other guy, but it didn't...

220
00:20:04,558 --> 00:20:06,140
we had to cut the movie

221
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:12,820
down from three hours, unfortunately, and that part never made it in.

222
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:30,300
So we're going to show the movie, and I said, don't we get a scene where he's like

223
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:39,560
being dunked underwater or something, waterboarded or something like that. And the editor said, can I do it to you?

224
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:43,560
That's part of the reshoots there, the waterboarding.

225
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:53,600
We really tried to walk a political line here, where we didn't really- we presented things pretty even-handedly, we didn't want to really

226
00:20:53,600 --> 00:21:05,040
vilify anyone, or present one side politically as wrong or right, but I thought the sense that he was a guy who was oblivious

227
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:16,420
to the effect that he had had in his life's work, takes sort of A Christmas Carol type approach to the storyline, not that he

228
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:18,380
becomes a pacifist per se, but he feels

